Executives of Gburugburu Disciples, led by the Director-General, Jonathan Chukwuma, the group’s Board of Trustees (BOT) Chairman, Prof. Simon Ortuanya, and royal fathers, who are the patrons, on Friday, reassured Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi of Enugu State of their support and loyalty in and out of office as governor, and even as he goes to the Senate, in keeping with the doctrine of their slogan: ‘Trust and Obey.’ The support group, whose membership is drawn from the 17 local councils of the state, said they love the governor’s exemplary leadership, appreciate his good works in the state and are resolute in supporting him “within and outside the office.” Presenting their stance when they paid a solidarity visit to the governor at the Government House, Enugu, Chukwuma said: “Your Excellency, we want to reassure you of our support and loyalty, both in the present government and even as you are going to the Senate. We are ready to work and serve you wherever you go. That’s why we said our ‘motto is Trust and Obey,”.